==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cultus
<hw>Cul"tus</hw> <pr>(k?l"t?s)</pr>, <pos>n. sing. & pl.</pos>;
<plu>E. pl. <plw>Cultuses</plw> <pr>(-<?/z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.,
cultivation, culture. See <er>Cult</er>.]</ety> <def>Established or
accepted religious rites or usages of worship; state of religious
development. Cf. <er>Cult</er>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cultus</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Cultus
<hw>Cul"tus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Cultus
cod</er>.]</ety> <def>Bad, worthless; no good.</def> <mark>[Northwestern
U. S.]</mark></p>

<p><q>⟦ldquo⟧A bad horse, <qex>cultus</qex> [no good] !⟦rdquo⟧ he said,
beating it with his whip.</q> <rj><qau>F. H. Balch.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cultus cod</ent>⟦br⟧
